<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,1724,2037]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1976,2001]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin word 
<taxonomicName box="[544,650,1976,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum">
<emphasis box="[544,650,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(mirror), in reference to the generally smooth and shiny body of females, one of the differentiating features for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
