<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
Putative relationships and differentiation of females of 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1089,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum">
<emphasis box="[945,1089,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1429,405,428]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropterus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1429,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. micropterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,308,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis box="[151,308,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. reticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[365,501,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distigma">
<emphasis box="[365,501,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. distigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are discussed under the latter species. Females most closely resemble those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. micropterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in most features, as discussed under the latter species, but have small paramedial depressions at the dorsal limit of the scrobal depression similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[686,819,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Eupelmidae" genus="Merostenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distigma">
<emphasis box="[686,819,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M. distigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
